es.csic.iiia.nsm.norm.reasoning

Class NormReasoner

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.csic.iiia.nsm.norm.reasoning.NormEngine
      • es.csic.iiia.nsm.norm.reasoning.NormReasoner
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.EventListener, jess.JessListener

    public class NormReasoner
extends NormEngine
    The norm reasoner employs the NormEngine (by extending it) to reason about norms applicability and compliance. It includes methods to compute which norms apply to the agents in a View, and to assess if the agents have complied or infringed norms in a transition of views (a ViewTransition)
    Author:
    "Javier Morales (jmorales@iiia.csic.es)"
    See Also:
    NormEngine, View, ViewTransition
